## 3. Available Data Streams

The following data streams are available in the enhanced system we are designing:

### 3.1 CGM: Continuous Glucose Monitor

- **Update frequency:** Every 5 minutes
- **Values available:** Current BG (mg/dL), trend arrow, raw signal
- **Derived values we can compute:** BG velocity (Δ mg/dL per minute), BG acceleration (Δ velocity per 5-min interval), BG jerk (Δ acceleration — useful for inflection point detection)
- **Noise characteristics:** CGM readings are noisy, particularly during compression artifacts and sensor warmup. A Kalman filter or exponential smoothing should be applied before using derivatives.

### 3.2 Pump: Insulin Delivery Data

- **IOB:** Continuously calculated from all recent boluses and temp basal adjustments, decayed using the configured DIA pharmacokinetic curve
- **Bolus history:** Time, amount, and type of every bolus
- **Basal history:** All temp basal rates set by oref
- **Extended boluses:** If used for high-fat/protein meals
- **This stream is already well-utilized by oref and remains unchanged**

### 3.3 Cronometer: Meal Macro Data

- **Integration method:** User logs meal in Cronometer → custom Trio integration reads macros via Cronometer API → one-tap entry into Trio treatments
- **Data available per meal:** Grams of carbohydrate, fat, protein, fiber; total calories; meal timestamp
- **What this unlocks:** Full macronutrient-aware absorption curve modeling, fat-protein tail prediction, personalized macro sensitivity learning over time

### 3.4 Garmin: Wearable Health Data

All Garmin data is available via the Garmin Connect API after sync (not real-time during most states). The following data streams are available:

#### Sleep Data (nightly)

- Total sleep duration
- Sleep stages: light, deep (slow-wave), REM, awake periods
- Sleep score (composite Garmin metric)
- Resting heart rate during sleep
- Overnight SpO2 (if supported by device)

#### HRV (Heart Rate Variability)

- HRV score (Garmin composite)
- Raw RMSSD values (where available)
- HRV status vs. 30-day baseline (Garmin categorizes as: poor, low, balanced, good)
- **This is the single most valuable daily recovery signal for insulin sensitivity estimation**

#### Body Battery

- Current value (0–100, Garmin composite of HRV, stress, sleep, activity)
- Charge/drain history throughout the day
- Useful as a secondary validation signal and user-facing explanation layer

#### Resting Heart Rate (daily)

- Daily resting HR measurement
- Trend vs. 7-day and 30-day baseline
- Elevated resting HR signals stress, illness, overtraining — all associated with insulin resistance

#### Saved Workouts

- Activity type (run, bike, strength, swim, HIIT, etc.)
- Start time, duration
- Average HR, max HR, HR zone distribution (% time in each zone)
- Distance, pace, power (sport-dependent)
- Estimated caloric expenditure
- Training effect score (aerobic and anaerobic)
- Garmin recovery time estimate

#### Daily Activity Summary

- Step count
- Active minutes by intensity
- Floors climbed
- Stress score (derived from HRV throughout the day)
- Intensity minutes

#### NOTE: Real-Time HR

Real-time heart rate **is not available** in the current integration. All Garmin data is post-sync. See Section 10 for a detailed discussion of what it would take to add live HR.

