## 7. The Daily State Vector

All of the above data streams feed into a unified **Daily State Vector** — a structured set of values that represents the user’s current physiological state and drives all algorithm parameter modifications.

The state vector is updated at key moments:

- **Morning refresh:** On first CGM reading of the day (after overnight sync of Garmin data)
- **Post-meal:** When Cronometer data is entered
- **Post-workout:** When a Garmin workout syncs
- **Every 5 minutes (partial update):** CGM-derived values (velocity, acceleration, residual)

```
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
DAILY STATE VECTOR  —  Example for a real day
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

RECOVERY & STRESS STATE
  Sleep duration last night:      6.2 hrs          (below 7.5 hr ideal)
  Deep sleep percentage:          14%              (below 20% normal)
