  - **Confirmatory signal:** 2+ consecutive readings with positive jerk (acceleration is itself increasing)
  - **Tertiary signal:** Velocity exceeds +2.0 mg/dL/min threshold (analogous to existing UAM detection)
- Confidence levels: `none` → `possible` (acceleration only) → `likely` (acceleration + velocity or jerk) → `confirmed` (all three signals active)
